      "bestPractice": [
        "Plan exclusion zones before the load is rigged, not while the load is already in the air.",
        "Use one clearly identified signal person unless the lift plan defines a transfer of control.",
        "Keep workers out from under suspended loads and away from pinch points at landing areas.",
        "Confirm load weight from a reliable source and include rigging weight where needed.",
        "Check wind, visibility, radio function, swing radius, ground conditions, and delivery routes.",
        "Use tag lines only when they reduce risk and do not pull workers into the load path.",
        "Pause the lift when any person loses sight, communication, or control of the load."
      ],
