        "Air monitoring or assessment record: supports follow-up if there is a deficiency, refusal, incident, or source-review question. {{cite:ohsr-part-8}}",
        "Respirator fit test/training record where required: shows workers received task-specific instruction before doing the work. {{cite:worksafebc-ohs-regulation}}",
        "Site-specific safe work procedure: keeps the field procedure tied to official sources instead of memory or habit. {{cite:worksafebc-silica}}",
        "Worker instruction or training record: helps employers, the prime contractor, and affected trades coordinate overlapping work. {{cite:worksafebc-ohs-guidelines}}",
        "Inspection or pre-use check record: gives the crew a reference point when conditions change mid-shift. {{cite:bccsa}}",
        "Corrective action record when a deficiency is found: creates evidence for the next scheduled safety/source review. {{cite:ohsr-part-5}}"
